{"TopicId":144735,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"BRI-Arrowhead, Stock-VTOL-SSTO-Spaceplane","CreatedByName":"Broco","CreatedById":4320,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T12:04:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Broco","CreatedById":4320,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T12:04:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter some real hard trial and error sessions I finally managed to build a pure stock \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E-Spaceplane with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E capabilities without any moving parts (aka no fancy docking port action): The BRI-Arrowhead!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022PrI1QSx.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022527\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/PrI1QSx.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022937\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAction groups:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1: RAPIER-engines toggle\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2: RAPIER-engines mode toggle\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3: Supersonic intakes toggle\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4: \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E-engines toggle\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n5: Whiplash engine toggle\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n6: Subsonic intakes toggle\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlight profile:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nactivate \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E (T) and go to full throttle\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nactivate \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E-engines (4)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nit takes some time for the engines to spin up, be patient\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nactivate the main engines (1 \u002B 5)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nclimb at an angle of ~15\u00B0 (prograde marker)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nonce you reach 400m/s speed, shut down the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E engines (4) and close the subsonic intakes (6)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nonce you reach 10000m, change your angle to ~5\u00B0 and gain speed. Once you reach 1200\u002B m/s, climb again at ~15\u00B0 (prograde marker)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nswitch to closed cycle after you reach 22000\u002B m\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\ndeactivate Whiplash engines (5) and close supersonic intakes (3)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nonce you reach 31 km, set autopilot to prograde marker\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\ncut engines once your apoapsis is above 100km\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nat apoapsis, circularize your orbit\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore Images (sorry about that, couldn\u0027t imbed the album here, so I just post a link:)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/4QwlM\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EArrowhead - Imgur\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCraft-File:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.file-upload.net/download-11816772/BRI-ArrowheadVTOL.craft.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EBRI-ArrowheadVTOL.craft\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022683\u0022 src=\u0022http://images.akamai.steamusercontent.com/ugc/259340219744722056/8B2FE9E9393062E90597D85DF09BECB159B6C943/\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 alt=\u00228B2FE9E9393062E90597D85DF09BECB159B6C943\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-02T11:09:03Z\u0022 title=\u002208/02/2016 11:09  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 2, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Broco\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EAdding images \u002B craft\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T14:23:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks awesome! Any more pics?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Unknown_Enemy","CreatedById":119738,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T17:17:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnice\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nany craft file ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Broco","CreatedById":4320,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-02T11:04:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222694631\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144735\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469715798\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 28.7.2016 at 4:23 PM, Majorjim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks awesome! Any more pics?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry about that, couldn\u0027t embed the Imgur album like before, I just put down a link to the album now. And sorry it took so long, was busy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222694808\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144735\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469726245\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119738\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Unknown_Enemy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 28.7.2016 at 7:17 PM, Unknown_Enemy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnice\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nany craft file ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYe sorry, forgot about that, I added it now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease note, you just get it into orbit of Kerbin, you need to refuel it or drag it to another planet. I built it mainly to fly around Laythe, due to the lower atmosphere and less gravity it\u0027s way easier to fly there and rendezvous in space to refuel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u002B For fun of course \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"qzgy","CreatedById":160994,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-02T11:54:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks very nice! I\u0027m curious, what did previous attempts look like?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Broco","CreatedById":4320,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-02T12:14:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222701315\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144735\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470138885\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160994\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022qzgy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, qzgy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks very nice! I\u0027m curious, what did previous attempts look like?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, I tried a lot of different setups, what you see here is the end of a 3 day long trial and error run. Basically I started with the design generally set up, since I built a lot of spaceplanes before. But having a spaceplane being able to carry all that additional weight, while being flight stable, having no flameouts and be able to lift the entire craft just with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E required a LOT of tweaking. I had to play with different intakes, different fuel tanks, realign engines etc. until I had a craft that was able to lift off barely with just \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E engines and make it into orbit. Dealing with flameouts was also a huge issue, since when you fly vertically you don\u0027t gain intake air.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne older version is this one but it didn\u0027t make it into orbit but was easier to fly at Kerbin:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022516\u0022 src=\u0022http://images.akamai.steamusercontent.com/ugc/259340219744889608/B89376AED9869E28D6D17629D3707896EDAAA57F/\u0022 width=\u0022918\u0022 alt=\u0022B89376AED9869E28D6D17629D3707896EDAAA57F\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut then again: Too many intakes, too much drag, not enough rocket fuel to make the final burn.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne hint I can give anyone who tries to make VTOLS though: create one section in your craft that holds all main \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E engines in a line so you can realign them without having to fine tune every single engine every time your center of mass moves due to changes to the craft, just move the whole engine set into the center of mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"X-SR71","CreatedById":108775,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-02T12:28:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks cool! Hey does closing the intakes do\u00A0anything (for the aerodynamic model)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-02T12:29:16Z\u0022 title=\u002208/02/2016 12:29  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 2, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by X-SR71\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Broco","CreatedById":4320,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-02T12:37:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222701350\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144735\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470140931\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022108775\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022X-SR71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, X-SR71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks cool! Hey does closing the intakes do\u00A0anything (for the aerodynamic model)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot yet, but in my opinion it should and it was meant to be implemented so that as soon as you close them you reduce drag. Before 1.0 it was the case but the aerodynamic model got changed a lot so that for example angle of attack now plays a huge role. Intakes should have a little bit less drag once they are closed that\u0027s why this function was implemented in the first place. I think it just takes some development time to adapt it to the new aerodynamics model.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m a programmer so when I design something I plan for it to work in coming patches \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn theory this craft should work even better once closing intakes reduces drag unless they take the opposite approach and increase drag on open intakes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-02T12:45:44Z\u0022 title=\u002208/02/2016 12:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 2, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Broco\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}